'''Anthony Paul Dostie''' (1821–1866) was a dentist and civil rights advocate who was killed in the [[New Orleans massacre of 1866]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://louisianadigitallibrary.org/islandora/object/state-lhp:3772|title=Anthony Paul Dostie|publisher=}}</ref> A book about his life was published in 1868 as ''The Life of A.P. Dostie'' or ''The Conflict in New Roads'' by his daughter Emily Hazen Reed. It is adorned with an [[engraving]] of Dostie by [[Augustus Robin]] of New York.
Dostie was born in [[Saratoga County]], New York.<ref> https://books.google.com/books?id=pnYglmWDN2UC&pg=PA360&lpg=PA360&dq=anthony+paul+dostie&source=bl&ots=LEQQAvPJCC&sig=-Im_8Rq6LgXzvgibK55I5OnMHSA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiAtJOXzcHZAhUBXqwKHT0_CJIQ6AEIUzAJ#v=onepage&q=anthony%20paul%20dostie&f=false</ref> ==References== {{Reflist}}
